      </section> -->

            <section class="slide col">
                <SlideTitle title="FAQs" />
                <div class="faqs">
                    <h4>Can you use the splint for Achilles tendonitis?</h4>
                    <p>
                        No, the splint is only used after rupture of the
                        Achilles tendon. It is not suitable for broken bones,
                        plantar fasciitis or Achilles tendonitis. The splint
                        holds the foot pointed downwards, in a tip toe position,
                        for tendon healing. For other conditions, like plantar
                        fasciitis and Achilles tendonitis, there are different
                        splints deliberately designed to do the opposite, and
                        hold the foot up.
                    </p>
                    <h4>Can you use the splint instead of a boot?</h4>
                    <p>
                        Yes, it is designed as an alternative - but ONLY for use
                        when resting. You cannot walk or stand in the splint
                        without crutches.
                    </p>
                    <h4>Is the sizing accurate?</h4>
                    <p>
                        Yes, the sizing is accurate. Sizing is based on foot
                        size, designed to ensure that the splint does not
                        interfere with the toes.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>
        </main>
    </body>
</Layout>
